Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

items.description:
Fine Motion (Umamusume) LoRA（LoCon）

The is LoRA using LoCon as convolution network, which can be loaded by using LoCon extension：GitHub - KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon

Install it through extension “Install from URL”, and you can use locon model as LoRA. (Put safetensor in LoRA folder)

You can learn more about LoCon from here.

Please use this with respect for the original content, DO NOT publish any NSFW content.

Recommended prompt:

For more accurate result, please use the following prompt for each outfit

Racing outfit

fine motion \(umamusume\), shoubufuku, white jacket, black bow, button, open clothes, green shirt, long sleeves, white gloves, black skirt, white socks, white footwear

Wedding dress

fine motion \(umamusume\), tiara, bridal veil, yellow hair ribbon, lace sleeves, long wedding dress, lace dress, high heels

Casual Wear

School uniform

fine motion \(umamusume\), natsufuku, sailor collar, puffy sleeves, short sleeves, purple bow, tracen school uniform, serafuku, white skirt, pleated skirt, white thighhighs, brown footwear

Prompt is broken down to more complicated one because condensed version was unable to reproduce certain clothing details properly.

*Use " socks ", "sandals", "thighhighs", "footwear" only while drawing lower body or full body, or it will force AI to draw in full body scale.

**Use "from behind", "ponytail" in negative prompt may help

Known problem

For unknown reason AI recognize hair bun as ponytail (mixed with horse tail?), add “short hair” in positive prompt while “ponytail” in negative prompt will help.

Racing outfit may generate white skirt (mixed with jacket) sometimes, add "white skirt" in negative prompt will help.

School uniform may mix with racing outfit sometimes, add "shobufuku" in negative prompt if necessary.

Adding "horse tail" will generate tail but dont expect on right place.

Again, Please use this with respect for the original content, DO NOT publish any NSFW content.

items.name: Eula Lawrence (Genshin Impact)
items.description:
One of the playable characters from Genshin Impact. Trained on AnythingV3 and tested to work with other traditional anime models as well. Works reasonably with the more shaded/3D anime models also. Can also recreate her sword quite nicely on still poses.

Basic prompt:
anime drawing of EulaLawrenceGI with blue_hair and yellow_eyes and purple_eyes

For further away shots the second eye-color is not necessary:
anime drawing of EulaLawrenceGI with blue_hair and yellow_eyes


The two-tone eye color might need a little bit of inpainting but usually easy to get it right with just a few tries. When doing images from further away you can get away with just "yellow_eyes" to avoid unnecessary color bleeding that is common with diffusion models.

Recommended strength: 0.8-1.0

The clothing is a bit sticky so if you want to do variety you should do it in two passes where you first lower the strength of the lora and then inpaint the head back in with full strength.

    • Racing competition clothes :

      • witch hat, black headwear, black necktie, collared shirt, red shirt, white gloves, wide sleeves, black jacket, black robe, buckle, belt, white skirt, pleated skirt, black thighhighs, thigh boots, black footwear, high heel boots

items.name: Debbie Harry from Blondie
items.description: Version 2 of this textual inversion renders Debbie Harry of Blondie pretty well. It is trained on photos of her from the 1977 - 1982 period. This model may not be used commercially. If you download the training data file, it has textual inversion files for every 10 training steps. I found that 3500 training steps was best (so it is the default), but often the 4500 training step model does better.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: Debbie Harry has one of the world's most uniquely symmetrical and well proportioned faces, which means that even small errors are really noticeable. As it happens, even a difference in a couple of hundred training iterations makes a big difference in how the images come out. I've packed all of the files, including the training checkpoints and different inversions with different numbers of training steps into a zip file that is attached as the "Training Data File". The main model used 3500 steps, but in many cases other numbers of steps give better results. The "training data" includes every number of training iterations, in steps of 10, from 10 to 4500. A few of the sample images show the same prompt as rendered on a textual inversion with a variety of iterations. If you install more than one of those other inversions, the tag would be "debbie_harry-####" where you replace #### with the number of inversions (so the 4500 inversion one would be debbie_harry-4500) I learned a lot doing this training, so hopefully my future efforts will be improved as well.

items.name: RealBiter
items.description:
This blend model aims to achieve versatility in generating images that are almost realistic but with a touch of fantasy and a polished aesthetic. It performs well with both illustrations and simulated photographs, but it particularly excels with the latter.

It is recommended to use an appropriate VAE to avoid color gradients, and the vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned model works especially well.

The blend includes the Offset Noise model, which enhances contrasts and black processing. Incorporating an Offset Noise LORA in image generation can further enhance the results.

The model is not specifically designed for NSFW content, but it easily generates this type of images.

The model has been reviewed with CLIP tensors checker and it shows no deviation.

Doesn't work on typical 2D Anime models, only realistic ones.

I might improve the embedding in the future or try to create Lora.

items.name: BeautyProMix
items.description:
關於BeautyProMix模型(人物及光影加強)

本模型經過約略1個月進行各項參數的調整並搭配大量的圖庫進行訓練，前後進行了近百次的混合及比例調整，此版本針對人像及光影表面十分令人讚賞(可參考示意圖的光影效果)。尤其是這個模型加入了BeautyPro首席穿搭顧問及彩妝師團隊的協助，針對用於訓練的每張照片進行細節的調整，使得面部表現更為優良。

感謝參與此模型製作的人員，包含製作者及提供照片作為模型訓練的朋友們，本模型搭配了多個主流模型進行訓練並條列如下，製作團隊已經盡力找到各個用於訓練模型的源頭，但難以確認每一個模型及每一張用於訓練的圖片是否存在版權疑慮，若我們的模型對您個人或公司的權益造成損害，請立即留言通知我們，製作團隊將立即將相關內容於模型中完全移除後，發布修正版本，謝謝。

#BeautyProMix
*為了感謝無日無夜測試模型的製作者團隊及無私提供照片的所有朋友，請於製作出來的圖片標註是採用 #BeautyProMix，僅代表製作者團隊群感謝您。

About the BeautyProMix Model(Enhancement of Characters and Lighting)

After approximately one month of adjusting various parameters and training with a large database of images, this model has undergone nearly 100 blends and ratio adjustments. This version focuses on enhancing the appearance of characters and lighting, and has received high praise. In particular, the model has incorporated the expertise of the BeautyPro team's chief fashion consultants and makeup artists to fine-tune the details of each photo used for training, resulting in superior detail of the face.

We would like to thank everyone who contributed to the production of this model, including the creators and friends who provided photos for training. The model was trained with multiple mainstream models, and we have made every effort to locate the sources of each model used for training. However, it is difficult to confirm whether each model or image used for training may have copyright concerns. If our model causes any damage to your personal or company interests, please inform us immediately. The developing team will promptly remove the relevant content from the model and release a corrected version. Thank you.

#BeautyProMix

*To express gratitude to the develop team who tirelessly tested the model day and night, and to all friends who generously provided photos, please tag the images produced using #BeautyProMix. This tag represents the collective appreciation of the developing team.

製作團隊正在收集更多願意提供用於訓練的人物照片或景色圖片，若您願意提供給BeautyPro團隊進行訓練，團隊將在共同製作者名單中，加入您的名字，以展示您對於AI繪圖及相關領域的付出及努力！

We need more quality Photos

The developing team is currently collecting more character portraits and scenic images from those willing to provide them for training. If you are willing to offer your photos to the BeautyPro team for training purposes, your name will be included in the list of co-creators to showcase your contribution and efforts to the field of AI drawing.

人物強化的進階版正在進行訓練中，若有更新的突破，我們將立即上傳提供大家測試及使用！若有任何建議及使用上的問題，也歡迎隨時留言，製作團隊感謝您提供的寶貴意見。
